don&#39;t do what I think you want them to do.

`periodicRate` and `months` get initialized to 0. However, they don&#39;t get updated when you read the values of `annualInterestRate` and `years` from user input.

You need to compute `periodicRate` and `months` after `annualInterestRate` and `years` have been read .

    float mortgage() {
    
        cout &lt;&lt; &quot;How much money do you want to borrow? (Nothing less than $100,000): &quot;;
